techmeme.title: At the DealBook Summit, Sundar Pichai said he would love to do a side-by-side comparison of Google and Microsoft's AI models, and expressed optimism about Trump (Nico Grant/New York Times)
Four Chinese state-backed industry groups, representing most of China's chip demand, urge members to drop US chips, calling them "no longer safe or reliable" (Reuters)
Enterpret, which lets companies automatically extract insights from customer feedback, raised a $20.8M Series A led by Canaan, bringing its total raised to $25M (Kyle Wiggers/TechCrunch)
At the DealBook Summit, Jeff Bezos said he is "very hopeful" about President-elect Donald Trump and praised his deregulatory agenda, and Elon Musk's leadership (New York Times)
Three members of Google's NotebookLM team, including its lead Raiza Martin, are leaving to launch a startup focused on building "a user-first AI product" (Charles Rollet/TechCrunch)
